from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, roc_auc_score

AUROC and ROC Curve

In [89]:
### Prediction Probabilities

r_probs = [0 for _ in range(len(y_test))]

lr1 = model.predict_proba(X_test)
knn1 = model2.predict_proba(X_test)
dt1 = model3.predict_proba(X_test)
rf1 = model4.predict_proba(X_test)
sv1 = model5.predict_proba(X_test)
nb1 = model6.predict_proba(X_test)

### Probabilities for the positive outcome is kept

lr1 = lr1[:,1]
knn1 = knn1[:,1]
dt1 = dt1[:,1]
rf1 = rf1[:,1]
sv1 = sv1[:,1]
nb1 = nb1[:,1]

### Computing AUROC and ROC curve values

r_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,r_probs)
lr1_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,lr1)
knn1_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,knn1)
dt1_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,dt1)
rf1_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,rf1)
sv1_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,sv1)
nb1_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test,nb1)

### Print AUROC scores

print('random prediction: AUROC = %.4f' % (r_auc))
print('Logistic Regression: AUROC = %.4f' % (lr1_auc))
print('knn: AUROC = %.4f' % (knn1_auc))
print('Decision Tree: AUROC = %.4f' % (dt1_auc))
print('Random Forest: AUROC = %.4f' % (rf1_auc))
print('Support vector machine: AUROC = %.4f' % (sv1_auc))
print('Naive bayes: AUROC = %.4f' % (nb1_auc))

### Calculate ROC curve

r_fpr, r_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,r_probs)
lr1_fpr, lr1_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,lr1)
knn1_fpr, knn1_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,knn1)
dt1_fpr, dt1_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,dt1)
rf1_fpr, rf1_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,rf1)
sv1_fpr, sv1_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,sv1)
nb1_fpr, nb1_tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test,nb1)

random prediction: AUROC = 0.5000
Logistic Regression: AUROC = 0.8166
knn: AUROC = 0.7478
Decision Tree: AUROC = 0.7105
Random Forest: AUROC = 0.7912
Support vector machine: AUROC = 0.6753
Naive bayes: AUROC = 0.7820

plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))

plt.plot(knn1_fpr , knn1_tpr, marker = '.', label = 'K-Nearest Neighbours (AUCROC = %0.3f)' % knn1_auc)

plt.plot(sv1_fpr , sv1_tpr, marker = '.', label = 'Support Vector Machine (AUCROC = %0.3f)' % sv1_auc)
